  "root_text": {
    "dhp221:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp221:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp221:0.3": "Kodhavagga ",
    "dhp221:0.4": "Rohinīkhattiyakaññāvatthu ",
    "dhp221:1": "Kodhaṁ jahe vippajaheyya mānaṁ, ",
    "dhp221:2": "Saṁyojanaṁ sabbamatikkameyya; ",
    "dhp221:3": "Taṁ nāmarūpasmimasajjamānaṁ, ",
    "dhp221:4": "Akiñcanaṁ nānupatanti dukkhā. ",
    "dhp222:0": "Aññatarabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp222:1": "Yo ve uppatitaṁ kodhaṁ, ",
    "dhp222:2": "rathaṁ bhantaṁva vāraye; ",
    "dhp222:3": "Tamahaṁ sārathiṁ brūmi, ",
    "dhp222:4": "rasmiggāho itaro jano. ",
    "dhp223:0": "Uttarāupāsikavatthu ",
    "dhp223:1": "Akkodhena jine kodhaṁ, ",
    "dhp223:2": "asādhuṁ sādhunā jine; ",
    "dhp223:3": "Jine kadariyaṁ dānena, ",
    "dhp223:4": "saccenālikavādinaṁ. ",
    "dhp224:0": "Mahāmoggallānapañhavatthu ",
    "dhp224:1": "Saccaṁ bhaṇe na kujjheyya, ",
    "dhp224:2": "dajjā appampi yācito; ",
    "dhp224:3": "Etehi tīhi ṭhānehi, ",
    "dhp224:4": "gacche devāna santike. ",
    "dhp225:0": "Buddhapitubrāhmaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp225:1": "Ahiṁsakā ye munayo, ",
    "dhp225:2": "niccaṁ kāyena saṁvutā; ",
    "dhp225:3": "Te yanti accutaṁ ṭhānaṁ, ",
    "dhp225:4": "yattha gantvā na socare. ",
    "dhp226:0": "Puṇṇadāsīvatthu ",
    "dhp226:1": "Sadā jāgaramānānaṁ, ",
    "dhp226:2": "ahorattānusikkhinaṁ; ",
    "dhp226:3": "Nibbānaṁ adhimuttānaṁ, ",
    "dhp226:4": "atthaṁ gacchanti āsavā. ",
    "dhp227:0": "Atulaupāsakavatthu ",
    "dhp227:1": "Porāṇametaṁ atula, ",
    "dhp227:2": "netaṁ ajjatanāmiva; ",
    "dhp227:3": "Nindanti tuṇhimāsīnaṁ, ",
    "dhp227:4": "nindanti bahubhāṇinaṁ; ",
    "dhp227:5": "Mitabhāṇimpi nindanti, ",
    "dhp227:6": "natthi loke anindito. ",
    "dhp228:1": "Na cāhu na ca bhavissati, ",
    "dhp228:2": "na cetarahi vijjati; ",
    "dhp228:3": "Ekantaṁ nindito poso, ",
    "dhp228:4": "ekantaṁ vā pasaṁsito. ",
    "dhp229:1": "Yañce viññū pasaṁsanti, ",
    "dhp229:2": "anuvicca suve suve; ",
    "dhp229:3": "Acchiddavuttiṁ medhāviṁ, ",
    "dhp229:4": "paññāsīlasamāhitaṁ. ",
    "dhp230:1": "Nikkhaṁ jambonadasseva, ",
    "dhp230:2": "ko taṁ ninditumarahati; ",
    "dhp230:3": "Devāpi naṁ pasaṁsanti, ",
    "dhp230:4": "brahmunāpi pasaṁsito. ",
    "dhp231:0": "Chabbaggiyavatthu ",
    "dhp231:1": "Kāyappakopaṁ rakkheyya, ",
    "dhp231:2": "kāyena saṁvuto siyā; ",
    "dhp231:3": "Kāyaduccaritaṁ hitvā, ",
    "dhp231:4": "kāyena sucaritaṁ care. ",
    "dhp232:1": "Vacīpakopaṁ rakkheyya, ",
    "dhp232:2": "vācāya saṁvuto siyā; ",
    "dhp232:3": "Vacīduccaritaṁ hitvā, ",
    "dhp232:4": "vācāya sucaritaṁ care. ",
    "dhp233:1": "Manopakopaṁ rakkheyya, ",
    "dhp233:2": "manasā saṁvuto siyā; ",
    "dhp233:3": "Manoduccaritaṁ hitvā, ",
    "dhp233:4": "manasā sucaritaṁ care. ",
    "dhp234:1": "Kāyena saṁvutā dhīrā, ",
    "dhp234:2": "atho vācāya saṁvutā; ",
    "dhp234:3": "Manasā saṁvutā dhīrā, ",
    "dhp234:4": "te ve suparisaṁvutā. ",
    "dhp234:5": "Kodhavaggo sattarasamo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp221:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp221:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 221–234 ",
    "dhp221:0.3": "17. Anger ",
    "dhp221:1": "Give up anger, get rid of conceit, ",
    "dhp221:2": "and escape every fetter. ",
    "dhp221:3": "Sufferings don’t befall one who has nothing, ",
    "dhp221:4": "not clinging to name and form. ",
    "dhp222:1": "When anger surges like a lurching chariot, ",
    "dhp222:2": "keep it in check. ",
    "dhp222:3": "That’s what I call a charioteer; ",
    "dhp222:4": "others just hold the reins. ",
    "dhp223:1": "Defeat anger with kindness, ",
    "dhp223:2": "villainy with virtue, ",
    "dhp223:3": "stinginess with giving, ",
    "dhp223:4": "and lies with truth. ",
    "dhp224:1": "Speak the truth, do not be angry, ",
    "dhp224:2": "and give when asked, if only a little. ",
    "dhp224:3": "By these three means, ",
    "dhp224:4": "you may enter the presence of the gods. ",
    "dhp225:1": "Those harmless sages, ",
    "dhp225:2": "always restrained in body, ",
    "dhp225:3": "go to the state that does not pass, ",
    "dhp225:4": "where there is no sorrow. ",
    "dhp226:1": "Always wakeful, ",
    "dhp226:2": "practicing night and day, ",
    "dhp226:3": "focused only on extinguishment, ",
    "dhp226:4": "their defilements come to an end. ",
    "dhp227:1": "It’s always been this way, Atula, ",
    "dhp227:2": "it’s not just today. ",
    "dhp227:3": "They blame you when you’re silent, ",
    "dhp227:4": "they blame you when you speak a lot, ",
    "dhp227:5": "and even when you speak just right: ",
    "dhp227:6": "no-one in the world escapes blame. ",
    "dhp228:1": "There never was, nor will be, ",
    "dhp228:2": "nor is there today, ",
    "dhp228:3": "someone who is wholly praised ",
    "dhp228:4": "or wholly blamed. ",
    "dhp229:1": "If, after watching them day in day out, ",
    "dhp229:2": "discerning people praise ",
    "dhp229:3": "that sage of impeccable conduct, ",
    "dhp229:4": "endowed with ethics and wisdom; ",
    "dhp230:1": "like a pendant of Black Plum River gold, ",
    "dhp230:2": "who is worthy to criticize them? ",
    "dhp230:3": "Even the gods praise them, ",
    "dhp230:4": "and by the Divinity, too, they’re praised. ",
    "dhp231:1": "Guard against ill-tempered deeds, ",
    "dhp231:2": "be restrained in body. ",
    "dhp231:3": "Giving up bad bodily conduct, ",
    "dhp231:4": "conduct yourself well in body. ",
    "dhp232:1": "Guard against ill-tempered words, ",
    "dhp232:2": "be restrained in speech. ",
    "dhp232:3": "Giving up bad verbal conduct, ",
    "dhp232:4": "conduct yourself well in speech. ",
    "dhp233:1": "Guard against ill-tempered thoughts, ",
    "dhp233:2": "be restrained in mind. ",
    "dhp233:3": "Giving up bad mental conduct, ",
    "dhp233:4": "conduct yourself well in mind. ",
    "dhp234:1": "An attentive one is restrained in body ",
    "dhp234:2": "restrained also in speech, ",
    "dhp234:3": "in thought, too, they are restrained: ",
    "dhp234:4": "they are restrained in every way. "
  },
